MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
A New Really Good Shew?: NBC and talk-show king Larry King are talking about 
doing a pilot for a prime-time series. 
According to King, he would host the live program weekly from the stage of a 
New York theater, featuring "newsmakers in the audience and new acts." But NBC 
officials denied suggestions that the project would be an Ed Sullivan-type 
variety show, describing it instead as an informational program. There is no 
deal yet; King said that the discussions started when NBC Entertainment 
President Brandon Tartikoff appeared on King's radio show. BETH KLEID 
